<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871110-0046 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Niagara Mohawk Power Corp.</HL><DD> 11/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NMKUTILITIES (UTI) </IN><TEXT>   Niagara Mohawk Power Corp. said the New York Public Service Commission plans to conduct a formal investigation of the utility's fossil-fuel purchasing practices.    The Syracuse, N.Y.-based utility said the commission staff believes Niagara Mohawk paid $100 million too much for its oil and coal over an unspecified period of time, and passed those overcharges through to ratepayers. Niagara Mohawk said the commission staff's claims were &quot;without substance.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>